msgctxt "mn120:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 120 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 120 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn120:0.2"
msgid "Saṅkhārupapattisutta "
msgstr "Rebirth by Choice "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn120:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn120:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "mn120:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn120:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn120:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn120:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn120:2.1"
msgid "“saṅkhārupapattiṃ vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi, "
msgstr "“I shall teach you rebirth by choice. "

msgctxt "mn120:2.2"
msgid "taṃ suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn120:2.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn120:2.4"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, pts-vp-pli3.100, sc2
msgctxt "mn120:3.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena samannāgato hoti, sutena samannāgato hoti, cāgena samannāgato hoti, paññāya samannāgato hoti. "
msgstr "“Take a mendicant who has faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom. "

msgctxt "mn120:3.2"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "They think: "

msgctxt "mn120:3.3"
msgid "‘aho vatāhaṃ kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā khattiyamahāsālānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘If only, when my body breaks up, after death, I would be reborn in the company of well-to-do aristocrats!’ "

msgctxt "mn120:3.4"
msgid "So taṃ cittaṃ dahati, taṃ cittaṃ adhiṭṭhāti, taṃ cittaṃ bhāveti. "
msgstr "They settle on that thought, stabilize it and develop it. "

#. VAR: tatrupapattiyā → tatrūpapattiyā (bj, s1-3, km) | tatruppattiyā (pts1)
msgctxt "mn120:3.5"
msgid "Tassa te saṅkhārā ca vihārā ca evaṃ bhāvitā evaṃ bahulīkatā tatrupapattiyā saṃvattanti. "
msgstr "Those choices and meditations of theirs, developed and cultivated like this, lead to rebirth there. "

msgctxt "mn120:3.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā tatrupapattiyā saṃvattati. "
msgstr "This is the path and the practice that leads to rebirth there. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4-5, sc3
msgctxt "mn120:4-5.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddhāya samannāgato hoti, sīlena samannāgato hoti, sutena samannāgato hoti, cāgena samannāgato hoti, paññāya samannāgato hoti. "
msgstr "Furthermore, take a mendicant who has faith, ethics, learning, generosity, and wisdom. "

